Example 1:

Input: n = 5
Output: 2
Explanation: 5 is "101" in binary, with complement "010" in binary, which is 2 in base-10.
----------------------------------


class Solution {
    public int bitwiseComplement(int n) {
        if(n==0) return 1;
        int Hbit=Integer.highestOneBit(n)<<1;
        return n^(Hbit-1);
    }
}
